<id>http://forums.nesdev.com/viewtopic.php?t=5875&amp;p=54372#p54372</id>
<link href="http://forums.nesdev.com/viewtopic.php?t=5875&amp;p=54372#p54372"/>
<title type="html"><![CDATA[SNES Konami Justifier Pinout?]]></title>

<content type="html" xml:base="http://forums.nesdev.com/viewtopic.php?t=5875&amp;p=54372#p54372"><![CDATA[
From the square end to the round end, the pinout for anything that plugs into a Super NES controller port is power, clock, strobe, data, data 2, data 3, ground. Data 3 is bidirectional; <a href="http://snesemu.black-ship.net/misc/techdocs/snestech.txt" class="postlink">this page</a> seems to indicate that the Super Scope and Justifier work by sending a pulse on data 3 when the CRT beam crosses the detector, causing PPU2 to latch the raster position just like on the Super Scope. So it might not be much more than a Zapper; if so, the trigger should show up on data or data 2. But you might want to read an existing Super NES emulator's input handling source code to make sure.<p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://forums.nesdev.com/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=9">tepples</a> — Thu Dec 24, 2009 10:42 am</p><hr />
]]></content>
